# Standardized AI ROI framework creates accountability across all initiatives
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Pre-Launch (Business Case)
  - Baseline measurement established before any AI investment
  - Target KPI defined: single primary metric per initiative
  - Holdout group designed for causal attribution
  - Break-even analysis: what outcome justifies the investment?
  - Stage-gate: no production deployment without approved business case

@col:
  ## Post-Launch (Value Tracking)
  - Monthly KPI dashboard for all production AI systems
  - Quarterly value realization review vs. business case
  - Escalation trigger: underperforming initiatives reviewed at 90 days
  - Annual portfolio pruning: bottom 20% of ROI investments discontinued
  - Attribution methodology: causal, not correlation-based

@notes: The holdout group discipline is the most important and most commonly skipped step. Without a control group, AI ROI is correlation, not causation — and correlation is useless for resource allocation.

